In an astounding move, Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane on Monday recommended that the Reserve Bank’s constitutional mandate be changed from protecting the value of the rand to a focus on the protection of “citizens’ socio-economic wellbeing”. The announcement sent the rand into a tailspin, with the local currency quickly weakening more than 2% against the dollar. Tampering with the mandate of the central bank is viewed extremely negatively by investors and credit ratings agencies, and as a threat to investment security. The recommendation is contained in Mkhwebane’s report into the government’s failure to recover apartheid-era funds extended to Bankorp, which was bought by Absa in 1992. If you are already a subscriber, please click on the following link below to go to the full article: Protector pushes for change in Bank’s role If you would like to subscribe  to BusinessLIVE Premium to read the full story, please click here: Subscribe * Premium content is not yet available on the app. Please use the desktop site to subscribe.